Ya fat, ya ugly, ya fugly.

01:42.969 --> 01:45.404
Max, we have got to get
more business going.

01:45.406 --> 01:47.086
The money Sophie gave us
to open the shop

01:47.087 --> 01:48.941
will only cover next month's rent.

01:48.943 --> 01:50.910
Wait, we already have
next month's rent?

01:50.912 --> 01:52.472
Why are we worried?
We're doing better

01:52.473 --> 01:54.664
than everyone else in America.

01:54.666 --> 01:58.650
Well, well, well,
if it isn't Prince Charming.

01:58.652 --> 02:00.753
But, Earl, is Prince Charming,

02:00.755 --> 02:04.423
or is he just a diva in purple?

02:04.425 --> 02:07.126
So psyched. Finally got
a personalized hello from Earl.

02:07.128 --> 02:08.461
He called me Prince Charming.

02:08.463 --> 02:10.795
I'm in, baby, I am in.

02:10.798 --> 02:12.014
I wouldn't get too excited.

02:12.016 --> 02:14.300
He probably just forgot your name.

02:14.302 --> 02:18.888
He calls every Puerto Rican guy
that comes in here "La Bamba."

02:21.358 --> 02:22.775
Max's Homemade Cupcakes.

02:23.277 --> 02:25.728
Yes, I'll hold.

02:25.730 --> 02:29.482
Of course we do sugar-free
and gluten-free.

02:30.484 --> 02:32.444
I'll be right back,
I just gotta take this call.

02:32.445 --> 02:35.788
Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm, I understand,
but, like, how diabetic?

02:35.790 --> 02:38.690
I feel a little sick to my stomach.

02:38.692 --> 02:41.410
Why? You haven't even
eaten here yet.

02:41.412 --> 02:42.995
No, I'm nervous.

02:42.997 --> 02:45.077
I came here to tell Caroline
something kind of big.

02:45.078 --> 02:47.249
What? You have
a secret family on Long Island?

02:47.251 --> 02:49.535
- No.
- You have Hep-C? "D"?

02:49.537 --> 02:52.004
- One of the new heps?
- No.

02:52.006 --> 02:53.506
I don't have any of the heps.

02:53.508 --> 02:55.257
Wow. Now, telling her
I'm in love with her

02:55.259 --> 02:56.708
is just going to sound boring.

02:57.210 --> 02:59.211
You're gonna tell her you love her?

02:59.213 --> 03:00.646
Here in the diner?

03:00.648 --> 03:03.983
Why, was the dump closed?

03:03.985 --> 03:07.553
Hey, we need more coffee, La Bamba.

03:07.555 --> 03:10.406
Andy, this isn't where
you tell someone "I love you."

03:10.408 --> 03:14.059
This is where you tell someone
their sex change looks passable.

03:14.061 --> 03:15.394
What's the big deal?

03:15.396 --> 03:16.996
If I feel it, why shouldn't I say it?

03:16.998 --> 03:18.564
I think she'd be all over that.

03:18.566 --> 03:20.783
Nope. If it didn't happen
to Kate Hudson

03:20.785 --> 03:22.084
in some stupid romantic comedy,

03:22.086 --> 03:24.036
then it won't work for Caroline.

03:24.538 --> 03:26.705
Sorry, what? I left
and went into another theater

03:26.707 --> 03:28.674
in my mind while you were talking.

03:29.376 --> 03:32.044
I know, it's so creepy,
but she likes it.

03:32.046 --> 03:34.079
Really, if you could
arrange for it to rain,

03:34.081 --> 03:36.048
or run after her
to the airport in the rain,

03:36.050 --> 03:38.300
but somehow end up on top
of the Empire State building

03:38.302 --> 03:40.603
on Valentine's Day, that'd be best.

03:40.605 --> 03:42.988
Well, I just sold three dozen cupcakes,

03:42.990 --> 03:45.526
we just have to mark "No sugar"
on one of the boxes.

03:49.595 --> 03:50.955
So what did you want to say to me?

03:50.956 --> 03:52.931
No, nothing, just came by to say hi.

03:52.933 --> 03:55.601
I gotta go download a couple movies.

03:56.303 --> 03:57.821
Hey, Oleg.
Where's my food?

03:59.923 --> 04:01.290
Cheeseburger with fries,

04:01.292 --> 04:03.775
pick-up.

04:03.777 --> 04:05.461
Han, you look so tall in the window.

04:05.463 --> 04:09.248
Tell me the truth, are you
standing on another tiny person?

04:11.617 --> 04:12.819
No.

04:15.505 --> 04:17.225
On the box.

04:19.927 --> 04:21.177
Oleg had to leave.

04:21.178 --> 04:22.978
Sophie came back
from her trip to Poland,

04:22.980 --> 04:25.731
and he's worried, 'cause
she's very, very depressed.

04:25.733 --> 04:28.134
Why, did she see you in that hair net?

04:28.136 --> 04:30.236
Come on, listen,
when Sophie went to see

04:30.238 --> 04:31.904
her new house, there was no house.

04:31.906 --> 04:34.857
Her Polish contractor
ripped off her money.

04:35.859 --> 04:38.444
Poor Sophie.
I feel terrible.

04:38.446 --> 04:40.329
I know what it feels like
to be ripped off.

04:40.331 --> 04:43.332
I once bought a Fendi purse,
but when I looked inside,

04:43.334 --> 04:45.984
it said "Rendi."

04:46.986 --> 04:50.539
What kind of god would let that happen?

04:51.041 --> 04:53.959
Max, I went to a party with that.

04:54.361 --> 04:56.295
We should stop by after work,
see how she is,

04:56.297 --> 04:58.297
and bring her
some of her favorite cupcakes.

04:58.299 --> 05:01.433
Or you could give her
that $20,000 she loaned you.

05:01.435 --> 05:04.186
Loaned us? Sophie gave us
that money as a gift.

05:04.188 --> 05:06.672
Not what I hear.
Pick-up!

05:07.174 --> 05:09.341
And we're out of spaghetti.
There's no sauce.

05:09.343 --> 05:11.009
No, Han, there's plenty of sauce.

05:11.011 --> 05:14.113
I know, but I can't reach the shelf.

05:18.718 --> 05:21.687
Hey, are we sure that money
Sophie gave us was a gift?

05:21.689 --> 05:24.540
Yes. She gave it to us
to support our dream.

05:24.542 --> 05:26.525
I know when I had money,
I gave it out freely,

05:26.527 --> 05:28.661
and never expected anything in return.

05:28.663 --> 05:31.413
Like when I gave my maid
that gorgeous Rendi.

05:31.915 --> 05:34.633
Well, I don't know about
people not expecting stuff back.

05:34.635 --> 05:36.201
One time, a guy bought me a slushy,

05:36.203 --> 05:38.837
and for the next three weeks,
he owned me.

05:38.839 --> 05:41.707
No, he really owned me.

05:41.709 --> 05:45.477
Eight days in, I almost
got traded to a trucker.

05:46.713 --> 05:48.347
And I wouldn't even mention her gift.

05:48.349 --> 05:50.382
It will only insult her, and I promise,

05:50.384 --> 05:53.903
nobody is expecting us
to give the money back.

05:53.905 --> 05:57.222
Come in, girls.
Did you bring the check?

05:57.224 --> 06:00.892
No, because it was a gift...
a big-ass gift,

06:01.394 --> 06:04.613
but we brought our love
and we brought cupcakes.

06:04.615 --> 06:06.699
Well, I doubt she'll eat them.

06:06.701 --> 06:10.052
She hasn't even touched her <i>kapusniak,</i>

06:10.054 --> 06:12.004
which is the dish traditionally served

06:12.006 --> 06:15.574
to Polish women who have been
wronged by their contractors.

06:16.976 --> 06:19.411
Such a specific culture.

06:19.413 --> 06:21.096
But that's not the worst thing.

06:21.098 --> 06:23.465
She is so depressed, no sex,

06:23.467 --> 06:25.100
which is big problem for me,

06:25.102 --> 06:29.305
because I find
depressed women very hot.

06:30.107 --> 06:31.607
A lot of guys do.

06:31.609 --> 06:34.760
Why do you think I haven't
paid for a drink in six years?

06:34.762 --> 06:37.196
I'll go in and tell her you're here.

06:37.198 --> 06:42.034
She's just lying there
on the bed, lifeless, hot...

06:42.036 --> 06:45.237
The big tease.

06:50.777 --> 06:52.777
Sophie, the two girls
who you loaned the money to

06:52.778 --> 06:54.747
are here to see you.

06:54.749 --> 06:56.582
It was a gift.

06:56.584 --> 06:59.117
A generous, generous gift,
but still a gift.

06:59.119 --> 07:01.453
Are we sure about that?
'Cause I was slushy boy's bitch

07:01.455 --> 07:04.807
for three weeks, and I did things.

07:04.809 --> 07:07.142
Look, Max brought you cupcakes,

07:07.144 --> 07:10.346
your favorite: Vanilla
with a bacon fat drizzle.

07:10.848 --> 07:14.566
No, I can't eat
when I've been betrayed.

07:14.568 --> 07:17.353
What kind again?

07:17.355 --> 07:21.106
Sophie, I am patient man,
but I am also horny man.

07:21.108 --> 07:23.609
Any idea when you will
snap out of this?

07:23.611 --> 07:27.479
Oh, why don't you just unzip
and climb on top of me now

07:27.481 --> 07:29.164
and get it over with?

07:29.166 --> 07:31.166
- Oh, no.
- Well, we should be going.

07:31.168 --> 07:33.035
No, girls, stay.

07:33.037 --> 07:36.755
If she's not even going to
put up a fight, what's the fun?

07:37.257 --> 07:38.674
Are you sure?

07:38.676 --> 07:41.427
Bacon drizzle, little bit of heaven.

07:41.429 --> 07:43.512
No, I don't want them.

07:43.514 --> 07:45.497
Okay, let's put the cupcakes here,

07:45.499 --> 07:47.299
in case you change your mind.

07:47.801 --> 07:50.019
- Is this a gun?
- Ooh!

07:50.021 --> 07:53.856
Yes. I'm not going to
stab myself to death.

07:53.858 --> 07:57.026
Do you know how much this outfit costs?

07:57.028 --> 07:59.010
Sophie, you're going to
get through this.

07:59.012 --> 08:01.697
And by the way,
you look amazing in black.

08:01.699 --> 08:05.234
Oh, well, no more
bright colors for me now.

08:05.236 --> 08:07.286
I'm in mourning.

08:07.288 --> 08:11.290
See?
Black bra, black garters,

08:11.292 --> 08:13.592
and look, black panties.

08:13.594 --> 08:17.379
Um, you're not wearing any panties.

08:17.381 --> 08:20.031
I'm not?

08:20.033 --> 08:21.417
Oh.

08:21.419 --> 08:24.803
I'm sorry about
that wild mess down there.

08:26.405 --> 08:28.891
Sophie, I feel bad you got ripped off.

08:28.893 --> 08:32.544
Here are all my tips $27.

08:32.796 --> 08:35.263
For eight hours?

08:35.265 --> 08:38.350
Oh, now, I'm depressed for you.

08:38.352 --> 08:40.969
You want to borrow my gun?

08:40.971 --> 08:43.638
You know what? I think
you just need to eat something,

08:43.640 --> 08:46.307
and pretty soon,
you'll be back to your old self:

08:46.309 --> 08:49.310
A woman who gives gifts
and expects nothing in return,

08:49.312 --> 08:51.997
'cause that's what a gift is.

08:53.783 --> 08:56.418
Sophie, is that doing anything for you?

08:56.420 --> 08:59.538
Yeah, well, I'm not hating it.

08:59.540 --> 09:02.758
Here, this soup smells amazing.

09:02.760 --> 09:05.043
Oh, no. I don't have
the energy to eat.

09:05.045 --> 09:08.447
Sophie, open your mouth
and put this in.

09:08.449 --> 09:12.634
Oh, come on.
Now you're as bad as Oleg.

09:12.636 --> 09:13.869
There. Better?

09:13.871 --> 09:16.855
That's cold.

09:16.857 --> 09:20.809
Sophie, just say the word,
and I will rob a bank for you.

09:20.811 --> 09:22.694
Sophie, I understand you're hurting,

09:22.696 --> 09:24.980
but we've already spent
most of the money on the shop,

09:24.982 --> 09:27.532
and business just isn't good.

09:27.534 --> 09:30.786
It's not the money.
Everybody thinks it's the money.

09:30.788 --> 09:32.320
It's more than that.

09:32.322 --> 09:35.540
My lake house was my dream,
and I lost my dream.

09:35.542 --> 09:36.875
Oh, thank God!

09:36.877 --> 09:39.044
Well, I'm glad that's cleared up.

09:39.046 --> 09:40.712
Not about the money.

09:40.714 --> 09:43.298
Max, come on, she's had a shock,
we should let her sleep.

09:43.300 --> 09:46.668
You girls are so lucky.
You still have your dream.

09:46.670 --> 09:49.304
Well, Sophie, what if you
were part of our dream?

09:49.306 --> 09:50.806
I'm sorry?
Whose dream?

09:50.808 --> 09:52.174
Our dream.

09:52.176 --> 09:55.877
Your dream?
Where's that cupcake?

09:55.879 --> 09:58.546
Look, Sophie's the only reason
we have a shop.

09:58.548 --> 09:59.988
We should make her, like, a partner.

09:59.989 --> 10:02.234
Mmm! Partner!

10:02.236 --> 10:04.352
But you and I are already partners.

10:04.354 --> 10:06.321
I feel like we're kind of
partnered out.

10:06.323 --> 10:08.023
What about a silent partner?

10:08.025 --> 10:11.559
Mmm! Silent partner!
Yeah, I like that.

10:11.561 --> 10:14.863
Mmm! I'm getting
my appetite back,

10:14.865 --> 10:17.866
and also, my sex drive.

10:18.618 --> 10:22.087
Go or stay, girls.
Either way, I'm going in.

