10:31.302 --> 10:33.869
I'm sorry I said Sophie
could be part of the store.

10:33.871 --> 10:36.005
I just felt bad for her, lying there,

10:36.007 --> 10:40.642
all in black, too sad
to even make her junk pretty.

10:40.644 --> 10:44.163
It's fine. "Silent partner" is
just a figurehead role anyway,

10:44.165 --> 10:46.699
and it's nice to know
you have such a big heart.

10:46.701 --> 10:47.933
It's not my heart.

10:47.935 --> 10:50.153
What I saw down there changed me.

10:52.155 --> 10:53.715
It looks like something an animal built

10:53.716 --> 10:56.058
to live in for the winter.

11:02.715 --> 11:05.784
Wait, what is
Sophie's chandelier doing here?

11:05.786 --> 11:08.303
Is this the Polish version
of a home invasion?

11:08.305 --> 11:11.273
They break in
and leave something tacky?

11:11.775 --> 11:14.459
Good morning, partners.

11:14.461 --> 11:18.597
I didn't know the dress code,
so I went business casual.

11:18.599 --> 11:23.852
Look, the chandelier that
I bought for my lake house.

11:23.854 --> 11:26.054
Oh, now our dreams are together.

11:26.056 --> 11:29.608
Sophie, it's not
the look we were going for.

11:29.610 --> 11:33.446
Oh, I know.
Much better, right?

11:33.998 --> 11:36.014
That is definitely not our style.

11:36.016 --> 11:39.968
It looks like a Tim Burton movie
just spit up in here.

11:39.970 --> 11:41.720
I think it's kind of pretty.

11:41.722 --> 11:43.222
But what do I know?

11:43.224 --> 11:46.558
I once spent my last 50 bucks
on a frog pinata.

11:46.560 --> 11:48.760
Had to have it.

11:50.564 --> 11:52.314
Max's Homemade Cupcakes.

11:52.316 --> 11:54.950
Yes, we're an upscale bakery, and...

11:54.952 --> 11:57.319
Now, we sell hoagies.

11:57.821 --> 12:00.289
Oh, no, no, no, sir,
we do not sell hoagies.

12:00.291 --> 12:01.957
Yes, we do.

12:02.959 --> 12:05.877
How many would you like?
Let me get a pen.

12:10.383 --> 12:11.667
What's happening?

12:11.669 --> 12:14.452
Are we finally gonna trash Caroline?

12:14.454 --> 12:15.804
No, I need your help.

12:15.806 --> 12:17.486
I watched four chick flicks
back-to-back,

12:17.487 --> 12:18.887
then I made a list of possible ways

12:18.888 --> 12:20.142
to tell Caroline I love her.

12:20.144 --> 12:24.096
I was gonna make more,
but I got my period.

12:25.598 --> 12:29.401
Okay, run the choices past me.

12:29.403 --> 12:31.436
Whichever one makes me
want to hurl the most,

12:31.438 --> 12:33.238
that's your winner.

12:33.240 --> 12:35.400
I could play a song for her
outside of her apartment,

12:35.401 --> 12:38.694
but keep in mind how hard it is
to find a boom box in 2012.

12:38.696 --> 12:40.979
Yeah, plus, if you do that
outside our apartment,

12:40.981 --> 12:42.648
you'll be shot.

12:42.650 --> 12:44.766
By me.

12:44.768 --> 12:47.953
Okay, what about
sharing cocoa and a hot dog

12:47.955 --> 12:49.654
on the ice rink in Central Park?

12:49.656 --> 12:50.956
Yup, that's it.

12:50.958 --> 12:52.374
Makes me want to take my head off

12:52.376 --> 12:53.625
and throw it into the street.

12:53.627 --> 12:55.858
Cool.
Oh, and, Max,

12:55.859 --> 12:57.579
I think I'm the only
straight guy on earth

12:57.580 --> 12:59.540
who knows the difference
between Dylan McDermott

12:59.541 --> 13:02.801
and Dermott Mulroney,
and that, my friend, is love.

13:04.987 --> 13:07.122
Oh, what's
that funky-ass smell?

13:07.124 --> 13:10.692
Do they finally sell pepperoni febreze?

13:11.194 --> 13:13.261
Max, this already isn't working.

13:13.263 --> 13:15.847
The stinky salami,
the gaudy chandelier?

13:15.849 --> 13:18.817
It's like a haunted Quiznos in here.

13:18.819 --> 13:21.953
Hey, I'm sending Oleg to Queens

13:21.955 --> 13:24.823
to pick up
a flat of Fresca. Yeah.

13:24.825 --> 13:26.425
There's nothing better with a hoagie

13:26.427 --> 13:28.493
than an ice-cold Fresca.

13:29.295 --> 13:31.029
That's what I wanted!

13:31.031 --> 13:32.914
Look...

13:32.916 --> 13:36.534
They'll go great with the pickled eggs!

13:38.270 --> 13:41.673
This just went from my dream
to a nightmare.

13:41.675 --> 13:44.393
Oh, my God, Caroline!
It is you!

13:44.395 --> 13:47.346
Stacy, no way! I haven't
seen you since graduation.

13:47.348 --> 13:49.031
We went to Wharton together.

13:49.033 --> 13:51.066
This girl is a genius.

13:51.068 --> 13:52.934
Always top of the class.

13:52.936 --> 13:54.519
So what are you doing here?

13:54.521 --> 13:57.389
Buying a cupcake on your way
to running the world?

13:57.391 --> 13:59.241
No, I own this shop.

13:59.243 --> 14:02.944
Oh. You own
this little cupcake shop?

14:02.946 --> 14:06.081
And many other bigger shops.

14:06.083 --> 14:08.333
This is our new Williamsburg location.

14:08.335 --> 14:10.452
And yes, I know,
the chandelier is all wrong.

14:10.454 --> 14:12.170
I told the designer, none of our

14:12.172 --> 14:15.073
Pacific Northwest locations
will have the chandeliers.

14:15.075 --> 14:18.710
Of course, you'd own
a cupcake empire at 25.

14:19.212 --> 14:21.546
- Oh, and this is Max.
- Hi.

14:21.548 --> 14:25.384
I just transferred
from our Boise location.

14:26.853 --> 14:28.937
What's that horrible smell?

14:29.439 --> 14:31.723
It's something called
a "hoagie."

14:31.725 --> 14:34.476
The workers like them.
Right, Max?

14:34.478 --> 14:39.431
<i>Si, gracias por la</i> hoagie.

14:39.433 --> 14:40.699
Well, I have to go.

14:40.701 --> 14:42.767
I'm consulting upstairs at BBD&L.

14:42.769 --> 14:44.653
- Oh, upstairs.
- Yeah.

14:44.655 --> 14:46.455
Always knew you'd land on your feet.

14:46.457 --> 14:50.459
Let's go for drinks,
and you're paying, mogul.

14:52.412 --> 14:55.163
I hope she likes water.

14:55.165 --> 14:58.250
Now what am I going to do?
Stacy's in the building.

14:58.252 --> 15:01.052
Well, you could move to Narnia
and run that branch,

15:01.054 --> 15:04.089
you pathological liar.

15:04.091 --> 15:06.892
Max, this is not
how I want people to see me,

15:06.894 --> 15:09.261
or smell me, quite frankly.

15:09.263 --> 15:11.629
We have to get rid
of the salami, the chandelier,

15:11.631 --> 15:13.932
and the Sophie.
This is our dream, not hers.

15:13.934 --> 15:15.817
Okay, fine, I'll tell her.

15:16.519 --> 15:19.237
Hey, Sophie, can we talk to you?

15:19.239 --> 15:20.939
Good news, girls.

15:20.941 --> 15:24.025
Now we sell scratchers.

15:24.727 --> 15:26.978
But I have even a better idea.

15:27.480 --> 15:30.782
You two should dress up as big cupcakes

15:30.784 --> 15:33.285
and pass out free samples.

15:36.121 --> 15:38.790
Sophie, Max has something
she wants to say to you.

15:38.792 --> 15:40.292
Wait.

15:40.294 --> 15:43.512
Girls, I have something to say first.

15:45.832 --> 15:50.835
Two days ago, I was
on the verge of suicide.

15:50.837 --> 15:54.506
Yeah, seriously,
I hadn't eaten all afternoon.

15:54.508 --> 15:58.176
But your generosity with your dream

15:58.178 --> 16:02.614
has given me a reason
to get up and get a wax.

16:02.616 --> 16:04.366
Yeah.

16:04.368 --> 16:09.154
Oh. Max, there was something
you wanted to say?

16:09.456 --> 16:12.325
I was going to say...

16:17.729 --> 16:19.215
You look delicious.

16:20.917 --> 16:23.868
I look like
Honey Boo Boo's mom at the prom.

16:31.690 --> 16:33.940
This is so humiliating.

16:33.942 --> 16:35.392
Now I know how Tyra felt

16:35.394 --> 16:37.978
when she went undercover
as that fat person.

16:37.980 --> 16:40.147
Please tell me this is our bottom.

16:40.149 --> 16:42.616
Well, it's your bottom.
I went to happy hour once

16:42.618 --> 16:44.618
and woke up naked
in the penguin habitat

16:44.620 --> 16:46.853
at the Bronx zoo.

16:46.855 --> 16:48.357
And I did things.

16:51.359 --> 16:52.742
Hey, girls.

16:52.744 --> 16:55.579
What are you two doing
just standing there?

16:55.581 --> 16:58.965
God gave cupcakes legs for a reason.

16:58.967 --> 17:01.084
You need to hit the streets,

17:01.086 --> 17:05.472
shake your cake maker,
and show people your goods.

17:05.473 --> 17:07.757
Hey, don't look at me, it's vanilla.

17:07.759 --> 17:09.559
I was looking forward to going up

17:09.560 --> 17:11.011
to complete strangers on the street

17:11.012 --> 17:14.347
and saying "eat me,"
but she won't leave.

17:14.348 --> 17:17.684
Well, if you're not going to
go out and get the customers,

17:17.685 --> 17:19.769
then I'll have to bring
the customers to you.

17:19.771 --> 17:23.056
I gotta do everything around here.

17:24.659 --> 17:26.790
Seriously, I can't believe
we're just standing here

17:26.791 --> 17:28.912
when we could be chasing
fat people down the street,

17:28.914 --> 17:32.565
yelling, "you ate my brother!"

17:32.567 --> 17:34.117
Look at you two.

17:34.119 --> 17:36.286
What I wouldn't give
for a giant glass of milk.

17:36.288 --> 17:37.671
Look at you, though.

17:37.673 --> 17:38.922
You look so cute.

17:38.924 --> 17:40.240
No, don't look at me.

17:40.242 --> 17:42.175
I'm totally embarrassed in this thing.

17:42.177 --> 17:44.844
Yes, she's cute and embarrassed,

17:44.846 --> 17:48.382
in a larger-than-life,
colorful, public setting.

17:49.884 --> 17:50.867
Ah, right.

17:50.869 --> 17:53.186
So, Caroline, listen, I wanted to...

17:53.188 --> 17:56.673
Look, girls, some young professionals.

17:56.675 --> 17:58.642
Oh, my God!
She's bringing Stacy.

17:58.644 --> 18:00.694
She can't see me in this.
I was her valedictorian.

18:00.696 --> 18:03.246
Take this.

18:05.483 --> 18:09.953
Oh! Ugh!
Oh! Wait.

18:09.955 --> 18:12.072
Help me up, Max!
Help me up!

18:12.074 --> 18:14.576
Oh, great.
Now you're like my mom.

18:16.578 --> 18:18.545
Here, give me your left hand.

18:19.547 --> 18:21.548
Okay, give me your right hand.

18:22.250 --> 18:25.335
Get up! Get up!
Five second rule.

18:33.894 --> 18:35.762
Ugh!

18:36.264 --> 18:38.631
What are you two crazy cakes doing?

18:38.633 --> 18:41.268
You lost your customers.
They ran away.

18:41.270 --> 18:43.069
Oh, thank God.

18:43.071 --> 18:44.604
Oh, I don't get it.

18:44.606 --> 18:47.324
You won't push the hoagies
or the pickled eggs.

18:47.326 --> 18:51.027
You must really have a fear of success.

18:52.730 --> 18:54.748
Well, at least we missed Stacy.

18:54.750 --> 18:57.367
Well, you know
what else you missed? Andy.

18:57.369 --> 18:59.485
He was about to tell you he loves you.

18:59.487 --> 19:00.820
What?

19:00.822 --> 19:03.156
Just now, in the hall,
and at the ice rink.

19:03.158 --> 19:05.125
He's been trying to tell you all week.

19:05.127 --> 19:07.210
But I've been
too preoccupied with work,

19:07.212 --> 19:11.348
like Sandra Bullock in <i>The Proposal.</i>

19:11.350 --> 19:14.050
So he was gonna tell me
at the ice rink?

19:14.052 --> 19:15.552
The one in Central Park?

19:15.554 --> 19:19.189
Yes, while having cocoa
and splitting a hot dog.

19:19.191 --> 19:20.673
Oh, my God!

19:20.675 --> 19:23.276
That's, like,
my dream "I love you" scenario.

19:23.778 --> 19:25.729
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

19:26.031 --> 19:27.781
Because when it comes to other people's

19:27.783 --> 19:31.117
creepy love stuff, that's
when I'm a silent partner,

19:31.119 --> 19:34.487
and you need to stop
with this creepy rom-com stuff.

19:34.489 --> 19:35.989
Life isn't like a movie.

19:35.991 --> 19:38.658
Sometimes you're not
a success right away

19:38.660 --> 19:41.211
sometimes you have to just
eat it and be a cupcake,

19:41.213 --> 19:43.696
and sometimes you have to
take your "I love you"

19:43.698 --> 19:45.632
whichever way it comes.

19:46.134 --> 19:47.584
You are so right.

19:47.586 --> 19:49.626
I don't have to wait
for the moment to be perfect,

19:49.627 --> 19:50.947
like it was for Reese Witherspoon

19:50.948 --> 19:53.973
in <i>Sweet Home Alabama.</i>

19:53.975 --> 19:56.209
My life's not a romantic comedy.

19:56.211 --> 19:57.811
I can do it my own way.

19:57.813 --> 20:00.681
Like Julia Roberts in
<i>My Best Friend's Wedding.</i>

20:08.656 --> 20:10.690
Andy, it's me!

20:10.692 --> 20:11.975
I'll be right out.

20:11.977 --> 20:13.510
No, this can't wait any longer.

20:13.512 --> 20:15.645
I don't need
a big romantic comedy moment.

20:15.647 --> 20:16.913
No...

20:16.915 --> 20:18.331
Oh!
Oh.

20:18.333 --> 20:19.999
Oh, sorry.
I thought it was the office!

20:20.001 --> 20:21.751
Not the office.

20:22.753 --> 20:24.037
I'm stuck.

20:24.039 --> 20:26.623
Oh, I want to go, but I can't.

20:26.625 --> 20:29.259
And I'll never be able to go again.

20:29.961 --> 20:32.762
Well, I'm on the toilet
and you're in a cupcake.

20:32.764 --> 20:36.099
Can't get creepier than this,
so, Caroline,

20:36.301 --> 20:38.101
I love you.

20:39.303 --> 20:41.738
I love you too.

20:42.773 --> 20:45.442
Oh, please, push me out.

20:49.096 --> 20:51.431
How'd it go?
Was it romantic?

20:51.433 --> 20:54.317
He told me he loved me on the toilet.

20:54.319 --> 20:57.070
Oh, man!
That's my dream scenario!

20:58.072 --> 20:59.322
Hey.

20:59.324 --> 21:01.624
I'm only gonna do this for an hour,

21:01.626 --> 21:03.626
to show you how it's done,

21:03.628 --> 21:05.628
and then I'm out.

21:05.630 --> 21:07.914
This is your dream, not mine.

21:07.916 --> 21:10.900
Cupcakes!
Free cupcakes!

21:11.402 --> 21:13.269
Come on, get 'em!

21:13.271 --> 21:15.457
Get 'em while they're hot!

